This paper deals with machine learning models and their fairness, which falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper proposes a novel algorithm that can identify and treat latent discriminating features, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). The paper also mentions regulatory compliance, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on real-world datasets, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
